<subSubSection pageNumber="346" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="346">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="346">Note:</emphasis>
This was treated as the 
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bauhinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="346">Bauhinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Britton &amp; Wilson (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="346">Bot. Porto Rico Virgin Is.</emphasis>
5: 362. 1924) (see McNeill &amp; al. in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="346">Taxon</emphasis>
36: 362. 1987). However, under Art. 10.5, Ex. 7 (a voted example) of the Vienna Code, this is a type choice made under the American Code and is to be replaced under Art. 10.5b by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hitchcock’s">Hitchcock's</normalizedToken>
choice (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="346">Prop. Brit. Bot.</emphasis>
: 152. 1929) of 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bauhinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divaricata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="346">B. divaricata</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
